{
  "texts": [
    "Customizing Memory Retention and Usage for Safe and Supportive ConversationsDuring the study, participants noticed that the chatbot did not consistently remember all their conversations (due to the memory limit set by OpenAI), and shared different perspectives regarding how they wanted the model to manage these past memories.",
    "They brought up the possibility of customizable memory settingsthe ways that the model retains and utilizes past conversationsfor tailored model performance, self-reflection, and privacy considerations.",
    "Behind these considerations were participants' selfawareness of their evolving emotional states and desires to receive explicit feedback about how their interactions with the chatbots could influence their emotional well-being.",
    "6.2.1Adjusting what to remember and what to forget to fulfill evolving user needs.",
    "Several participants wanted to remove conversations containing negative content to avoid revisiting it in future interactions (P12, P13, P17, P19, P20, P21)."
  ]
}